-- French Stocks: Alcatel-Lucent, CGGVeritas, Saint-Gobain Move
-- B y   D a v i d   A l t a n e r
-- 2010-10-11T16:00:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/edf-gdf-suez-l-oreal-total-vivendi-french-equity-preview.html
France’s  CAC 40 Index  rose 5.31, or
0.1 percent, to 3,768.49 at the 5:30 p.m. close in Paris. The
SBF 120 Index also gained 0.2 percent to 2,809.93.  The following shares rose or fell in the French capital.
Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Alcatel-Lucent SA  (ALU FP) increased 1.8 percent to 2.59
euros. The telecommunications-equipment maker has no plans to
further restructure the company, Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer  Ben Verwaayen .  CGGVeritas  (GA FP) slipped 2.4 percent to 16.39 euros, a
third day of losses. The world’s largest seismic surveyor of
oilfields was downgraded to “hold” from “buy” at Societe
Generale SA.  Cie. de Saint-Gobain  (SGO FP) gained 2 percent to 34.01
euros. The glassmaker expanded into the photovoltaic industry by
setting up a joint venture with Hyundai Heavy Industries Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Altaner in London at 
 daltaner@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
